LineNo: 10762063,

Narrator: On the banks of the Zpana River in...
en


On the banks of the Zpana River in Bronaz stood Palas Verana.

LineNo: 10762165,

Narrator: Almost as opulent as my own palace,...
en


Almost as opulent as my own palace, it had once served as a summer residence for my ancestors, the Rubaz family.

LineNo: 10762267,

Narrator: Today it was the home of Russello ...
en


Today it was the home of Russello "Rusty" Montoro. The CEO of Rizian Royal Gold, and the wealthiest commoner in the country.

LineNo: 10762369,

Narrator: I stepped out onto the deck of the...
en


I stepped out onto the deck of the Rizania as the yacht approached the palace's private dock. Hugo and Elena were already there, gazing out at the grounds.

LineNo: 10762471,

Hugo Toras: I can't believe what I'm seeing. P...
en


"I can't believe what I'm seeing. Palas Verana without its water garden is no palace at all."

LineNo: 10762573,

Elena Werner: I think it's an improvement, mysel...
en


"I think it's an improvement, myself. But what do you make of this, Your Majesty?"

LineNo: 10762675,

Narrator: I looked in the direction she was i...
en


I looked in the direction she was indicating. The water garden, once a tranquil oasis filled with blossoming flowers and gently burbling fountains, had been replaced with a gigantic gold-tiled swimming pool.

LineNo: 10762801,

Player_Romus: Hideous. I hate new money.
en


"Hideous. I hate new money."

LineNo: 10762903,

Player_Romus: Seems practical. I never understoo...
en


"Seems practical. I never understood the appeal of water gardens anyway."

LineNo: 10763005,

Player_Romus: Why don't we have one of these at...
en


"Why don't we have one of these at Palas Rezna?"

LineNo: 10763107,

Hugo Toras: Because we have taste.
en


"Because we have taste."

LineNo: 10763209,

Elena Werner: They're attractive, to be sure. Bu...
en


"They're attractive, to be sure. But in the height of summer, looking at fountains you can't swim in is just torturous."

LineNo: 10763311,

Hugo Toras: I'd be surprised if Mr. Montoro ev...
en


"I'd be surprised if Mr. Montoro even used it."

LineNo: 10763413,

Narrator: The gold magnate's red hair was str...
en


The gold magnate's red hair was streaked with grey, but his eyes had a youthful mischief about them.

LineNo: 10763515,

Russello Montoro: On behalf of all of us at the este...
en


"On behalf of all of us at the esteemed Rizian Royal Gold corporation, I do hereby extend my cordial greetings..."

LineNo: 10763617,

Narrator: He trailed off with a grin.
en


He trailed off with a grin.

LineNo: 10763719,

Russello Montoro: Heck, I was never one for formalit...
en


"Heck, I was never one for formalities. Welcome to my palace, Your Majesty."

LineNo: 10763845,

Player_Romus: It's a pleasure, Rusty.
en


"It's a pleasure, Rusty."

LineNo: 10763947,

Player_Romus: Thank you, Mr. Montoro.
en


"Thank you, Mr. Montoro."

LineNo: 10764049,

Player_Romus: You certainly have made it yours,...
en


"You certainly have made it yours, haven't you?"

LineNo: 10764151,

Russello Montoro: Oh, the pool? I can't stand swimmi...
en


"Oh, the pool? I can't stand swimming myself. Get sunburned at the drop of a hat. The grandkids love it, though."

LineNo: 10764253,

Narrator: He turned to Hugo and Elena.
en


He turned to Hugo and Elena.

LineNo: 10764355,

Russello Montoro: Your Grace, Madam Treasurer. Haven...
en


"Your Grace, Madam Treasurer. Haven't had a sit-down with you two since the last man wore the crown."

LineNo: 10764457,

Hugo Toras: You must mean my honorable brother...
en


"You must mean my honorable brother, His Majesty King Valero. May he rest in peace."

LineNo: 10764559,

Narrator: My uncle gritted his teeth.
en


My uncle gritted his teeth.

LineNo: 10764661,

Elena Werner: Now, Hugo. Rusty paid his respects...
en


"Now, Hugo. Rusty paid his respects at the funeral like everyone else."

LineNo: 10764763,

Narrator: She shook Rusty's hand. He beckoned...
en


She shook Rusty's hand. He beckoned for us to sit as his butlers brought over water and fresh fruit.

LineNo: 10764881,

Russello Montoro: Name's Rusty. Calling me 'Mr. Mont...
en


"Name's Rusty. Calling me 'Mr. Montoro' is like trying to put an elevator in an outhouse."

LineNo: 10764983,

Russello Montoro: You know there would be no Rizia w...
en


"You know there would be no Rizia without Rizian Royal Gold."

LineNo: 10765101,

Russello Montoro: And continues to do so even as we...
en


"And continues to do so even as we speak."

LineNo: 10765203,

Russello Montoro: My point being, it's fair to say t...
en


"My point being, it's fair to say that what concerns me concerns this country."

LineNo: 10765305,

Russello Montoro: And right now, what concerns me is...
en


"And right now, what concerns me is this."

LineNo: 10765407,

Narrator: He picked up a piece of paper from...
en


He picked up a piece of paper from the table next to him. It was a flyer with a few sentences written in both Rizian and Wehzek.

LineNo: 10765509,

Player_Romus: A Malenyevist. A dangerous figure.
en


"A Malenyevist. A dangerous figure."

LineNo: 10765611,

Player_Romus: The first female Prime Minister of...
en


"The first female Prime Minister of Morella. A pioneer."

LineNo: 10765713,

Player_Romus: She's not a threat.
en


"She's not a threat."

LineNo: 10765815,

Russello Montoro: A pioneering pain in our behind.
en


"A pioneering pain in our behind."

LineNo: 10765917,

Russello Montoro: Right, Your Majesty. Banning propa...
en


"Right, Your Majesty. Banning propaganda in Rizia won't stop what's happening on her side of the border."

LineNo: 10766019,

Russello Montoro: Woman's never picked up a chisel i...
en


"Woman's never picked up a chisel in her life, and she suddenly knows how to run the MITZ."

LineNo: 10766399,

Russello Montoro: That's right, Your Majesty.
en


"That's right, Your Majesty."

LineNo: 10766501,

Russello Montoro: She wouldn't be if she stuck to go...
en


"She wouldn't be if she stuck to governing Morella. You know, like she was elected to do."

LineNo: 10766603,

Russello Montoro: Supervisors at my mines are pickin...
en


"Supervisors at my mines are picking up hints that the workers are holding after-hours meetings. On the subject of 'unsafe conditions'."

LineNo: 10766721,

Player_Romus: Have you tried, I don't know, impr...
en


"Have you tried, I don't know, improving those conditions?"

LineNo: 10766823,

Player_Romus: They should be grateful to be empl...
en


"They should be grateful to be employed at all."

LineNo: 10766925,

Player_Romus: The first step to unionizing?
en


"The first step to unionizing?"

LineNo: 10767027,

Russello Montoro: Don't know if I'd go that far. But...
en


"Don't know if I'd go that far. But meeting workers' demands is like feeding zoo animals. The more you give them, the hungrier they get."

LineNo: 10767129,

Russello Montoro: They were before. Someone's been p...
en


"They were before. Someone's been putting ideas in their heads."

LineNo: 10767231,

Russello Montoro: Meeting workers' demands is like f...
en


"Meeting workers' demands is like feeding zoo animals. The more you give them, the hungrier they get."

LineNo: 10767333,

Elena Werner: Have there been any accidents late...
en


"Have there been any accidents lately? Anything that might have triggered this?"

LineNo: 10767435,

Narrator: Rusty snorted.
en


Rusty snorted.

LineNo: 10767537,

Russello Montoro: Accidents have been part of this j...
en


"Accidents have been part of this job since the dawn of time. Used to say you weren't a real miner until you were missing a finger."

LineNo: 10767655,

Player_Romus: That's barbaric.
en


"That's barbaric."

LineNo: 10767757,

Player_Romus: What do you need all ten of them f...
en


"What do you need all ten of them for, anyway?"

LineNo: 10767859,

Player_Romus: Did you ever even work in the mine...
en


"Did you ever even work in the mines yourself, Rusty?"

LineNo: 10767961,

Russello Montoro: As long as you've got enough to sw...
en


"As long as you've got enough to swing a pickaxe."

LineNo: 10768063,

Russello Montoro: Not extensively. But I've swung a...
en


"Not extensively. But I've swung a pickaxe or two in my day."

LineNo: 10768165,

Russello Montoro: Not all of us are lucky enough to...
en


"Not all of us are lucky enough to sit on thrones our entire lives."

LineNo: 10768267,

Narrator: Hugo cleared his throat.
en


Hugo cleared his throat.

LineNo: 10768369,

Hugo Toras: Do you have a request of His Majes...
en


"Do you have a request of His Majesty, Mr. Montoro? Or have you merely invited us here to complain?"

LineNo: 10768471,

Russello Montoro: Not complain. Warn.
en


"Not complain. Warn."

LineNo: 10768573,

Russello Montoro: RRG's value has been going down si...
en


"RRG's value has been going down since we lost Zille. New safety regulations might sound fine and dandy, but they'd be a death blow to our bottom line."

LineNo: 10768675,

Player_Romus: How much revenue would we stand to...
en


"How much revenue would we stand to lose?"

LineNo: 10768777,

Player_Romus: We still have the Meftiem Internat...
en


"We still have the Meftiem International Trade Zone, don't we?"

LineNo: 10768879,

Player_Romus: Your company will rebound when we...
en


"Your company will rebound when we get Zille back."

LineNo: 10768981,

Russello Montoro: Hard to say. Implementing the regu...
en


"Hard to say. Implementing the regulations themselves would cost a pretty penny."

LineNo: 10769083,

Russello Montoro: And what do you think will happen...
en


"And what do you think will happen if we pass those costs on to our trading partners? They'll hit the road faster than my first ex-wife."

LineNo: 10769185,

Russello Montoro: Well, that's the other thing.
en


"Well, that's the other thing."

LineNo: 10769287,

Russello Montoro: I'm sure you know all about Alma S...
en


"I'm sure you know all about Alma Saltana."

LineNo: 10769405,

Russello Montoro: I sure hope that's in the cards, Y...
en


"I sure hope that's in the cards, Your Majesty."

LineNo: 10769507,

Narrator: Elena raised her eyebrows.
en


Elena raised her eyebrows.

LineNo: 10769609,

Elena Werner: We have been seeing more global co...
en


"We have been seeing more global competition on the gold market, unfortunately."

LineNo: 10769711,

Player_Romus: Aren't most of your miners labor h...
en


"Aren't most of your miners labor hands from foreign countries? Would the regulations even apply to them?"

LineNo: 10769813,

Elena Werner: Morella doesn't have unilateral po...
en


"Morella doesn't have unilateral power over the International Trade Zone. Rizia, Lespia and Valgsland all have a say."

LineNo: 10769915,

Russello Montoro: And guess which one of those Ms. S...
en


"And guess which one of those Ms. Saltana has been cozying up to on this subject?"

LineNo: 10770017,

Russello Montoro: If she and Hegel get their way, Ri...
en


"If she and Hegel get their way, Rizia will either lose its mining rights or our boys will have to pray to Malenyev before going to work every morning."

LineNo: 10770143,

Player_Romus: Actually, Malenyev is a staunch at...
en


"Actually, Malenyev is a staunch atheist."

LineNo: 10770245,

Player_Romus: That still leaves us and Lespia.
en


"That still leaves us and Lespia."

LineNo: 10770347,

Player_Romus: She should have the right to deter...
en


"She should have the right to determine how gold is mined in her own country."

LineNo: 10770449,

Gold Regs Hub
Title en


Gold Regs Hub

LineNo: 10770575,

Russello Montoro: They most certainly would, now tha...
en


"They most certainly would, now that labor hands have the same protections as honest-to-goodness Rizians."

LineNo: 10770677,

Russello Montoro: That little nub of land is home to...
en


"That little nub of land is home to some of the fattest gold veins my company's ever found. No way Wehlen could mine it all in 25 years."

LineNo: 10770779,

Hugo Toras: It's Chancellor Hegel's influence...
en


"It's Chancellor Hegel's influence that is concerning. Malenyevism has a way of spilling over borders."

LineNo: 10770881,

Elena Werner: It's hard to say if we can count o...
en


"It's hard to say if we can count on Lespia's cooperation. Of course they abhor Valgsland, but we don't have the friendliest history with them either."

LineNo: 10770983,

Hugo Toras: Another reason to keep his influen...
en


"Another reason to keep his influence far from our borders."

LineNo: 10771085,

Player_Romus: No matter what, our revenue from t...
en


"No matter what, our revenue from the region takes a hit."

LineNo: 10771187,

Hugo Toras: And the CSP will claim another vic...
en


"And the CSP will claim another victory."

LineNo: 10771289,

Elena Werner: The political aspect isn't as conc...
en


"The political aspect isn't as concerning to me as the loss of access to our most important mines. We have to keep a close eye on this."

LineNo: 10771391,

Russello Montoro: She's started calling for regulati...
en


"She's started calling for regulation over there as well. Or worse, nationalization."

LineNo: 10771493,

Elena Werner: We'll have to keep a close eye on...
en


"We'll have to keep a close eye on this."

LineNo: 10771595,

Russello Montoro: Honestly, Your Majesty, I just abo...
en


"Honestly, Your Majesty, I just about ate my hat when you made that decree."

LineNo: 10771697,

Russello Montoro: I lost enough money granting all k...
en


"I lost enough money granting all kinds of benefits to folks who don't even understand how lucky they are to work here. Giving them more would damn near bankrupt me."

LineNo: 10771799,

Elena Werner: A little extreme, don't you think?
en


"A little extreme, don't you think?"

LineNo: 10771901,

Elena Werner: I agree we shouldn't impose more r...
en


"I agree we shouldn't impose more regulations than necessary, but investing in safer and healthier employees could lead to profit in the long term. Foreigners included."

LineNo: 10772003,

Player_Romus: I'd say the partnership between yo...
en


"I'd say the partnership between your company and the monarchy has benefited both of us equally."

LineNo: 10772105,

Player_Romus: Yes, RRG has contributed greatly t...
en


"Yes, RRG has contributed greatly to Rizia's wealth."

LineNo: 10772207,

Player_Romus: Don't overinflate your importance....
en


"Don't overinflate your importance. We have other resources."

LineNo: 10772309,

Russello Montoro: Sure, Your Majesty.
en


"Sure, Your Majesty."

LineNo: 10772411,

Russello Montoro: But only one is in the name of the...
en


"But only one is in the name of the national anthem."

LineNo: 10772513,

Player_Romus: So what's the occasion?
en


"So what's the occasion?"

LineNo: 10772615,

Player_Romus: I suppose you haven't invited us o...
en


"I suppose you haven't invited us over here to marvel at your renovations."

LineNo: 10772717,

Player_Romus: So how's business?
en


"So how's business?"

LineNo: 10772819,

Russello Montoro: Neat, aren't they? But no.
en


"Neat, aren't they? But no."

LineNo: 10772921,

Russello Montoro: I couldn't help noticing you've be...
en


"I couldn't help noticing you've been crisscrossing the kingdom lately. And no royal tour would be complete without a visit to your old friend Rusty."

LineNo: 10773023,

Russello Montoro: A shame Her Highness couldn't make...
en


"A shame Her Highness couldn't make it. Too occupied with her latest beau?"

LineNo: 10773125,

Hugo Toras: One dance does not a 'beau' make....
en


"One dance does not a 'beau' make. We'll thank you not to speculate about Princess Vina's romantic prospects."

LineNo: 10773243,

Russello Montoro: We'll get to that, Your Majesty. S...
en


"We'll get to that, Your Majesty. Settle down, have a drink first."

LineNo: 10773345,

Player_Romus: Please tell me what this meeting i...
en


"Please tell me what this meeting is about, Rusty. We don't have all day."

LineNo: 10773447,

Player_Romus: That's quite all right, Hugo. My d...
en


"That's quite all right, Hugo. My daughter does happen to have her eye on a special someone."

LineNo: 10773549,

Player_Romus: Agreed. We're keeping the topic of...
en


"Agreed. We're keeping the topic of my daughter's love life within the family."

LineNo: 10773651,

Russello Montoro: Lucky man. Anyway, I'll cut to the...
en


"Lucky man. Anyway, I'll cut to the chase."

LineNo: 10773753,

Russello Montoro: Well, all right.
en


"Well, all right."

LineNo: 10773855,

Narrator: He sat back and unbuttoned the top...
en


He sat back and unbuttoned the top button of his shirt.

LineNo: 10773957,

Elena Werner: But for now, our product is of hig...
en


"But for now, our product is of high enough quality that Rumburg is willing to pay more for it."

LineNo: 10774059,

Hugo Toras: Yes, but if the price rises furthe...
en


"Yes, but if the price rises further still? I'd rather not admit it, but Mr. Montoro may have a point."

LineNo: 10774161,

Elena Werner: You're saying that RRG's mining op...
en


"You're saying that RRG's mining operations in the region could pick up where they left off?"

LineNo: 10774263,

Russello Montoro: Yes, ma'am. Assuming we got it bac...
en


"Yes, ma'am. Assuming we got it back without making too much of a mess."

LineNo: 10776467,

Russello Montoro: Look, you know me. I don't mince w...
en


"Look, you know me. I don't mince words."

LineNo: 10776569,

Narrator: Rusty took a big bite out of a wate...
en


Rusty took a big bite out of a watermelon slice. He wiped the juice off his chin.

LineNo: 10776671,

Russello Montoro: I think you already realize that i...
en


"I think you already realize that it's in both of our interests for you to back me up in this squabble."

LineNo: 10776773,

Narrator: Elena pushed her chair back and sto...
en


Elena pushed her chair back and stood up.

LineNo: 10776875,

Player_Romus: So are you trying to bribe the gov...
en


"So are you trying to bribe the government, Mr. Montoro?"

LineNo: 10776977,

Player_Romus: It seems like RRG is in trouble an...
en


"It seems like RRG is in trouble anyway. Of course you're eager to sell it off."

LineNo: 10777079,

Russello Montoro: But hey, I'll sweeten the deal. Ke...
en


"But hey, I'll sweeten the deal. Keep your administration's nose out of RRG's business, and I'll sell you back the share I took from your father."

LineNo: 10777181,

Russello Montoro: Name's Rusty. And what I'm suggest...
en


"Name's Rusty. And what I'm suggesting is completely above-board. Just a little handshake between shareholders."

LineNo: 10777307,

Russello Montoro: Gold is gold. Long as you let us k...
en


"Gold is gold. Long as you let us keep doing things the way we always have, there'll be plenty of money to be made."

LineNo: 10777433,

Player_Romus: You're willing to sell us back 15...
en


"You're willing to sell us back 15 percent of RRG? Just for refusing to pass regulations?"

LineNo: 10777535,

Russello Montoro: Why not? It's about time we put 'R...
en


"Why not? It's about time we put 'Royal' back in RRG. Partially, anyway."

LineNo: 10777661,

Elena Werner: I'm going to recuse myself from th...
en


"I'm going to recuse myself from this conversation. Where is the ladies' room?"

LineNo: 10777763,

Russello Montoro: Just inside. If you've never sat o...
en


"Just inside. If you've never sat on a solid gold toilet, you're in for a treat."

LineNo: 10777865,

Narrator: She forced a smile as a butler esco...
en


She forced a smile as a butler escorted her out. Hugo, Rusty and I glanced at each other.

LineNo: 10777991,

Hugo Toras: What you're proposing is incredibl...
en


"What you're proposing is incredibly crass, *Rusty*."

LineNo: 10778093,

Narrator: He looked at me.
en


He looked at me.

LineNo: 10778195,

Hugo Toras: But increasing the state's share i...
en


"But increasing the state's share in RRG would serve us well. Besides which, giving in to workers' demands might embolden them to a dangerous degree."

LineNo: 10778297,

Player_Romus: I accept. I'll make sure no new re...
en


"I accept. I'll make sure no new regulations pass on mining, and you'll let the Kingdom alter its stake in RRG."

LineNo: 10778303,

Player_Romus: I accept. I'll make sure no new re...
Menu Text en


"I accept. I'll make sure no new regulations pass on mining, and you'll let the Kingdom alter its stake in RRG." [Accept Bribe]

LineNo: 10778405,

Player_Romus: I must refuse. If our workers want...
en


"I must refuse. If our workers want protections, I will be obliged to grant to them."

LineNo: 10778507,

Player_Romus: I'll keep my hands off your mining...
en


"I'll keep my hands off your mining operations, Rusty. But I won't accept what you're offering."

LineNo: 10778513,

Player_Romus: I'll keep my hands off your mining...
Menu Text en


"I'll keep my hands off your mining operations, Rusty. But I won't accept what you're offering, either."

LineNo: 10778615,

Narrator: Rusty shrugged.
en


Rusty shrugged.

LineNo: 10778717,

Russello Montoro: Suit yourself, Your Majesty. The o...
en


"Suit yourself, Your Majesty. The offer still stands if you change your mind."

LineNo: 10778819,

Narrator: Rusty shrugged.
en


Rusty shrugged.

LineNo: 10778921,

Russello Montoro: Suit yourself.
en


"Suit yourself."

LineNo: 10779023,

Narrator: Rusty smiled.
en


Rusty smiled.

LineNo: 10779125,

Russello Montoro: Perfect. This could be the beginni...
en


"Perfect. This could be the beginning of something beautiful."

LineNo: 10779227,

Narrator: Elena stepped back into the room.
en


Elena stepped back into the room.

LineNo: 10779329,

Elena Werner: That was colder than I expected. A...
en


"That was colder than I expected. Are you gentlemen finished?"

LineNo: 10779431,

Narrator: Hugo practically sprang from his se...
en


Hugo practically sprang from his seat.

LineNo: 10779533,

Player_Romus: Any opinions on this, Hugo?
en


"Any opinions on this, Hugo?"

LineNo: 10779635,

Russello Montoro: You're a smart man, Your Grace. Yo...
en


"You're a smart man, Your Grace. You and I should go out for beers someday."

LineNo: 10779737,

Narrator: Hugo looked like he'd swallowed som...
en


Hugo looked like he'd swallowed something unpleasant.

LineNo: 10779839,

Hugo Toras: It's been a delight, truly, but we...
en


"It's been a delight, truly, but we must be headed back to Porte Drazon."

LineNo: 10779941,

Russello Montoro: And here I was about to ask you to...
en


"And here I was about to ask you to stay for lunch. So soon, Your Majesty?"

LineNo: 10780059,

Player_Romus: Yes, we've done what we set out to...
en


"Yes, we've done what we set out to do here."

LineNo: 10780161,

Player_Romus: Don't worry. You'll be hearing fro...
en


"Don't worry. You'll be hearing from me."

LineNo: 10780263,

Player_Romus: Please excuse my uncle's hastiness...
en


"Please excuse my uncle's hastiness. Lunch would be lovely."

LineNo: 10780365,

Player_Romus: Remind me. How did a man like him...
en


"Remind me. How did a man like him take over the most powerful corporation in Rizia?"

LineNo: 10780467,

Elena Werner: He's got a knack for being in the...
en


"He's got a knack for being in the right place at the right time."

LineNo: 10780569,

Hugo Toras: Legend has it he worked his way up...
en


"Legend has it he worked his way up from regional mine supervisor via a series of backroom deals and boardroom betrayals."

LineNo: 10780671,

Russello Montoro: I'm not going to change a thing ab...
en


"I'm not going to change a thing about the way my mines operate. So sooner or later, this is going to land in your lap."

LineNo: 10780773,

Narrator: Rusty cracked a triumphant smile.
en


Rusty cracked a triumphant smile.

LineNo: 10780875,

Russello Montoro: Sorry, Your Grace. Got to pretend...
en


"Sorry, Your Grace. Got to pretend to be civil to me a while longer."

LineNo: 10780977,

Russello Montoro: That we have. Enjoy the trip back.
en


"That we have. Enjoy the trip back."

LineNo: 10781373,

Russello Montoro: That you have. Enjoy the trip back.
en


"That you have. Enjoy the trip back."

LineNo: 10781491,

Russello Montoro: Not if you hear from me first, eh,...
en


"Not if you hear from me first, eh, Your Majesty?"

LineNo: 10781601,

Player_Romus: See you, Rusty.
en


"See you, Rusty."

LineNo: 10781703,

Player_Romus: Goodbye, Mr. Montoro.
en


"Goodbye, Mr. Montoro."

LineNo: 10781805,

Player_Romus: Until next time.
en


"Until next time."

LineNo: 10781907,

Narrator: I could see him cheerfully waving f...
en


I could see him cheerfully waving from the veranda as Hugo, Elena and I stepped back on board the yacht.

LineNo: 10782009,

Narrator: Hugo and Elena sat back down as the...
